# Project structure

Application code lives under `src/`. Use the `@/` path alias (`@/` → `src/`) for all internal imports — never deep relative paths like `../../`.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
import { Button } from '../../components/Button/Button';

// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from '@/components';
import { useUserStore } from '@/stores';
import { colors, spacing } from '@/theme';
```

## Folder responsibilities

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `src/components/` | Reusable UI primitives |
| `src/screens/` | Full-screen views |
| `src/navigators/` | Navigation containers and stacks |
| `src/services/` | API domains (e.g. `posts/`) with fetchers and React Query hooks |
| `src/stores/` | Zustand stores and MMKV persistence |
| `src/theme/` | Design tokens (colors, spacing, typography, borders) |
| `src/translations/` | i18next setup and locale files |
| `src/types/` | Shared TypeScript types (navigation, i18n) |
| `src/utils/` | Helpers and test utilities |

## Barrel exports

Re-export public APIs from each folder's `index.ts`. Import from the barrel, not from internal file paths.

- `src/components/index.ts` — UI components
- `src/screens/index.ts` — screen components
- `src/stores/index.ts` — store hooks
- `src/services/<domain>/index.ts` — React Query hooks and keys per API domain

Root app wiring stays at the repo root: `App.tsx`, `index.js`, native `ios/` and `android/`.
